<sec>
<st>
Demographics</st>
<p>

The population of the area is approx. 4.200 people. Before the introduction of tourism and greenhouses, the life revolved mainly up in the villages, which you find nestled  in the mountains. A lot of them are not visible from the sea, for this reason they were  safe from pirates. Back in the early days the main work for the villagers was farming or tending their flocks on the higher peaks. Today, life revolves around the coast. People have come down from the villages to the coast to live, as there is more work in the towns and resorts. The older generations still live up in the villages along with their history and old stories. Also foreigners who have bought old houses, using them as holiday homes are settling in the old charming villages.</p>
<p>

The main industry today around Makrigialos is tourism, greenhouses and the harvesting of the olive trees. The Cretan dialect spoken in this region is near to ancient Greek.</p>
